- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an end-to-end training scheme for discovering discrete subword units from speech, which involves machine learning techniques. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper involves the use of an ASR-TTS autoencoder and adversarial training, which are techniques related to artificial intelligence. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): Although the paper does not deal with computer vision, it is possible that it could be categorized under this sub-category due to the use of adversarial training, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision tasks.
